
[1]perceivable

   PERCE'IVABLE, a. [See Perceive.] Perceptible; that may be perceived;
   that may fall under perception or the cognizance of the senses; that
   may be felt, seen, heard, smelt or tasted. We say, the roughness of
   cloth is perceivable; the dawn of the morning is perceivable; the sound
   of a bell is perceivable; the scent of an orange is perceivable; the
   difference of taste in an apple and an orange is perceivable.

   1. That may be known,understood or conceived. [Less proper.]
